NYT of May 31, 1914 reports on this event and has other photos.
  <a href="http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F60C1FFD345D13738DDDA80B94DD405B848DF1D3" rel="nofollow">query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F60C1FFD345D13738...</a>
&quot;HORSES AND DRIVERS HONORED FOR MERIT; Police and Fire Departments Easily Lead in the Annual Show of Work Animals.&quot;  There is special mention of special applause when the &quot;heavy engine of Company 14 came up, drawn by three big white horses, Lightfoot, Reporter, and Jim, 16, 12, and 10 years old.&quot;
